### Advanced RAG API Examples
### Use with REST Client extension in VS Code or similar tools

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000/api

### 1. Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### 2. Upload PDF Document
POST {{baseUrl}}/documents/upload
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW

------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="document.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./sample-document.pdf
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="category"

technical
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="author"

John Doe
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="tags"

["ai", "rag", "vector-search"]
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW--

### 3. Process Text Directly
POST {{baseUrl}}/documents/text
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "text": "Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) is a technique that enhances large language models by providing them with relevant context from external knowledge sources. This approach helps reduce hallucinations and improves the factual accuracy of generated responses. RAG systems typically consist of four main components: an embedding model for converting text to vectors, a vector database for storing and retrieving information, a prompt template for structuring queries, and a generative LLM for producing answers.",
  "metadata": {
    "category": "education",
    "author": "AI Researcher",
    "tags": ["rag", "llm", "ai"],
    "description": "Introduction to RAG systems"
  }
}

### 4. Standard Query with All Optimizations
POST {{baseUrl}}/query
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "What are the main components of a RAG system and how do they work together?",
  "options": {
    "useQueryRewriting": true,
    "useHybridSearch": true,
    "useReranking": true,
    "topK": 10,
    "rerankTopK": 5
  }
}

### 5. Simple Query (No Optimizations)
POST {{baseUrl}}/query/simple
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "What is semantic chunking?",
  "topK": 5
}

### 6. Query with Decomposition (Complex Question)
POST {{baseUrl}}/query/advanced
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "How does hybrid search combine vector and keyword search, and what are the advantages of each approach?",
  "useQueryRewriting": true,
  "useQueryDecomposition": true,
  "useHybridSearch": true,
  "useReranking": true,
  "useCoT": true,
  "topK": 20,
  "rerankTopK": 5
}

### 7. Query with Expansion (Exploratory)
POST {{baseUrl}}/query/advanced
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "embedding models",
  "useQueryExpansion": true,
  "useHybridSearch": true,
  "useReranking": true,
  "topK": 15,
  "rerankTopK": 5
}

### 8. Query with Metadata Filter
POST {{baseUrl}}/query/advanced
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "What are the best practices for chunking?",
  "useHybridSearch": true,
  "useReranking": true,
  "metadataFilter": {
    "category": "technical",
    "tags": ["rag"]
  },
  "topK": 10
}

### 9. Query with Context Compression
POST {{baseUrl}}/query/advanced
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "Explain re-ranking in RAG systems",
  "useQueryRewriting": true,
  "useHybridSearch": true,
  "useReranking": true,
  "useContextCompression": true,
  "topK": 20,
  "rerankTopK": 5
}

### 10. Intelligent Query Routing
POST {{baseUrl}}/query/route
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "Compare and contrast different chunking strategies and explain when to use each one"
}

### 11. Chain of Thought Query
POST {{baseUrl}}/query/advanced
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "Why is metadata filtering important in RAG systems and how does it improve retrieval quality?",
  "useQueryRewriting": true,
  "useHybridSearch": true,
  "useReranking": true,
  "useCoT": true,
  "topK": 15
}

### 12. Get Document Statistics
GET {{baseUrl}}/documents/stats

### 13. Delete Document
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/documents/your-document-id-here

### 14. Factual Query (Auto-routed)
POST {{baseUrl}}/query/route
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "What is the default embedding dimension?"
}

### 15. Complex Query (Auto-routed)
POST {{baseUrl}}/query/route
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "How do I implement a RAG system that handles both technical documentation and conversational queries while maintaining high accuracy?"
}

### 16. Query with Date Filter
POST {{baseUrl}}/query/advanced
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "Recent developments in RAG",
  "useHybridSearch": true,
  "metadataFilter": {
    "dateFrom": "2024-01-01",
    "dateTo": "2024-12-31"
  },
  "topK": 10
}

### 17. Minimal Query (Vector Search Only)
POST {{baseUrl}}/query/advanced
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "What is prompt engineering?",
  "useQueryRewriting": false,
  "useQueryExpansion": false,
  "useQueryDecomposition": false,
  "useHybridSearch": false,
  "useReranking": false,
  "useContextCompression": false,
  "useCoT": false,
  "topK": 5
}

### 18. Maximum Optimizations
POST {{baseUrl}}/query/advanced
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "What are all the optimization techniques available in advanced RAG systems?",
  "useQueryRewriting": true,
  "useQueryExpansion": true,
  "useQueryDecomposition": false,
  "useHybridSearch": true,
  "useReranking": true,
  "useContextCompression": true,
  "useCoT": true,
  "topK": 25,
  "rerankTopK": 7
}

